    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_07cd545d",
      "file_path": "controlloop/common/eventmanager/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/controlloop/eventmanager/ControlLoopOperationManagerTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 141,
      "message": "You are correct, but for whatever reason, the table created in\n\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=policy/drools-applications.git;a=blob_plain;f=controlloop/common/guard/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/guard/PIPEngineGetHistoryTest.java;hb=48eb8e2bd1674592ddfadfbbc01a611b6a263393\n\nis never dropped.  I initially attempted to fix that code by adding a 'drop table' in an AfterClass method, but for whatever reason that didn't seem to fix the problem and I didn't have time to pursue the matter further.  \n\nI see several options:\n1) I can work on fixing the erroneous code in guard first and then resubmit this test for review.\n2) I can remove the commented out code for setting up the table here.\n3) I can add a comment explaining the issue.\n\nPlease let me know which of these (or another) you'd like.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 423,
        "name": "Joshua Reich",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jreich@research.att.com",
        "username": "josh.reich"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-27 21:56:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_61051879",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_c772fc10",
      "file_path": "controlloop/common/eventmanager/src/test/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 32,
      "message": "The biggest thing that was wrong w/ Derby was that it wasn't actually being used.  The output of the tests contained a bunch of derby-related errors.  The first problem was that the pom hadn't even included a dependency for Derby!  I tried fixing that, but some other errors then arose.  Instead of trying to get Derby working for the first time, I switched to using the same setup as https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=policy/drools-applications.git;a=blob_plain;f=controlloop/common/guard/src/test/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml;hb=HEAD\nwhich had the added bonuses of both working properly and making the DB-related test code in eventmanager consistent with the DB-related test code in guard.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 423,
        "name": "Joshua Reich",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jreich@research.att.com",
        "username": "josh.reich"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-27 21:56:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_41025c70",
      "unresolved": false
    },
